Package gui

Provides classes for the graphical user interface, corresponding to the View in the Model-View-Controller architecture
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BorrowLoans
    Class implementing a BorrowLoans window as part of the GUI for taking loans from the bank
    ChooseCareerCard
    Class implementing a ChooseCareerCard window as part of the GUI for choosing a career card
    ChooseHouse
    Class implementing a ChooseHouse window as part of the GUI for choosing a house
    ChoosePath
    Class implementing a ChoosePath window as part of the GUI for choosing a life path
    ChoosePlayer
    Class implementing a ChoosePlayer window as part of the GUI for choosing another player
    ChooseSalaryCard
    Class implementing a ChooseSalaryCard window as part of the GUI for choosing a salary card
    EndScreen
    Class implementing an EndScreen window as part of the GUI for concluding the game
    ErrorDialogLoan
    Class implementing the graphical user interface for the error dialog displayed when an invalid number of loans is entered by the player
    ErrorDialogPlayerNames
    Class implementing the graphical user interface for the error dialog displayed when invalid or duplicate usernames are entered by the players
    GenericInfo
    Class implementing a GenericInfo window as part of the GUI for displaying game events
    InitPlayerNames
    Class implementing the graphical user interface for the screen asking for the usernames of the players at the start of the game
    JPanelWithBG
    Class implementing a JPanelWithBG, used to set the background for the board of the game
    MainScreen
    Class implementing a MainScreen window as part of the GUI for the game
    PayLoans
    Class implementing a PayLoans window as part of the GUI for paying loans to the bank
    SeeAllCards
    Class implementing a SeeAllCards window as part of the GUI for displaying all the players' cards at the beginning of the game
    SeeCards
    Class implementing a SeeCards window as part of the GUI for displaying all the cards kept by a player
    SeeRules
    Class implementing a SeeRules window as part of the GUI for displaying the rules of the game
    SpinWheel
    Class implementing a SpinWheel window as part of the GUI for asking the player to spin the number wheel
    WelcomeScreen
    Class implementing the graphical user interface for the welcome screen at the start of the game
